---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import site from '../data/site.json';
---
<Base
  title="About — Joshua Herrington"
  description="I climbed to managing director of an international planning firm — and I'm walking away to build something that runs on my values, my story, and my standard. This is the why."
>
  <article class="about">
    <div class="wrap">
      <a class="back" href="/">← imua.space</a>
      <span class="kicker">About</span>
      <h1>I keep my promises.<br /><span class="em">I expect the same.</span></h1>
      <p class="lead">
        I climbed to Managing Director, North America at an international planning firm. This
        week I'm walking away from it — to build something that runs on my values, my story,
        and my standard. Here's the why.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="band">
      <img src="/images/hero/kyrgyzstan.webp" alt="Joshua Herrington" loading="lazy"
           onerror="this.parentElement.style.background='#dfe9f4'" />
    </div>

    <div class="wrap body">
      <h2>From the missile field to the Court of the Table</h2>
      <p>I left home at twelve and have been building myself ever since — a ranch, the United States Air Force, a kitchen, a sales floor. The Air Force gave me a standard and a set of men who held it. The rest I earned the hard way.</p>
      <p>I tasted the world — Japan, Europe, Canada — and came home to serve the people who build this country. What I do now is move people, money, and systems forward, and I write it all down as it happens. Not the polished retrospective. The field notes of someone still in it.</p>

      <h2>What I built</h2>
      <p>As Managing Director, North America, I lead distribution for an international financial-planning firm that serves ultra-high-net-worth families whose lives and wealth cross borders — work that reaches across Europe, the Gulf, and Korea. I advise the advisors who serve some of the most internationally connected families in the world.</p>
      <p>I lead a team of six and a year-round program of twenty interns drawn from USC, Cal Poly, and UCLA. I qualified MDRT and reached Court of the Table. I build the tools my advisors plan and sell with, and I coach the conversations that win the business. By every external measure, I made it.</p>

      <h2>Why I'm leaving</h2>
      <p>I hold one rule I won't bend: do what you say, and say what you'll do — maybe more, never less. I gave that climb everything — the eighteen-hour days, the standard held when no one was watching. And I learned that the people at the top of it couldn't keep the one promise that mattered.</p>
      <p>So I'm walking away from the most I've ever earned. Because none of the climb is worth the trade if it costs you the thing you were climbing for.</p>

      <blockquote class="pull">
        I'd rather keep my word and start over than keep the title and lose it.
      </blockquote>

      <h2>What's next</h2>
      <p>I'm building it on me. A book — <em>IMUA</em>, written as it happens. A set of working tools that show exactly how I operate as a sales executive. A site that says plainly who I am and what I stand for. This is that — and it's only the beginning.</p>
      <div class="ctas">
        <a class="cta" href={site.bookUrl}>Read the book →</a>
        <a class="cta ghost" href="/#work">See how I work →</a>
        <a class="cta ghost" href={site.substackUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Follow Becoming →</a>
      </div>

      <h2 id="press">Press &amp; Media</h2>
      <p>If you want the story in my own voice, start with the podcast. The rest is where my work shows up in the field.</p>

      <div class="podcast">
        <span class="show">{site.podcast.show}</span>
        <h3>“{site.podcast.title}”</h3>
        <p class="pmeta">{site.podcast.meta}</p>
        <div class="listen">
          <span class="listen-label">Listen on</span>
          {site.podcast.links.map((l) => (
            <a class={l.primary ? 'plat primary' : 'plat'} href={l.href} target="_blank" rel="noopener">{l.label}</a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <ul class="press-list">
        {site.press.map((p) => (
          <li><a href={p.href} target="_blank" rel="noopener">{p.label} →</a></li>
        ))}
      </ul>

      <h2>What it's for</h2>
      <p>I have a blended family and a narrow window to be present for it — a little girl who's started calling me dad, two dogs, and a lot of road. I figured out what matters in time to still spend it where it matters.</p>
      <p>The debt stops here — for my kids, and for me.</p>
      <p class="values">Guided by five values: {site.values.join(' · ')}.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .about { background: var(--cream); padding: 40px 0 80px; }
  .about .wrap { max-width: 760px; }
  .back { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; }
  .back:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .about .kicker { display: block; margin-top: 26px; color: var(--ember); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px; font-size: 12px; }
  .about h1 { font-size: clamp(34px, 7vw, 52px); line-height: 1.04; letter-spacing: -.015em; margin-top: 12px; }
  .about h1 .em { color: var(--ember); }
  .about .lead {
    font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(17px, 2.6vw, 21px); line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--ink); margin-top: 18px; max-width: 56ch;
  }

  .band {
    max-width: 980px; margin: 34px auto 0; height: clamp(220px, 42vw, 380px);
    border-radius: 16px; overflow: hidden; border: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .band img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; object-position: center 38%; display: block; }

  .body { margin-top: 40px; }
  .about h2 {
    font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(22px, 3.4vw, 28px); margin-top: 38px;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }
  .about h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .about p { margin-top: 14px; font-size: 16.5px; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--ink); }
  .about em { font-style: italic; }

  .pull {
    margin: 32px 0 8px; border-left: 3px solid var(--ember); padding: 6px 0 6px 22px;
    font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(20px, 3.2vw, 26px); line-height: 1.3; color: var(--brown);
  }

  .ctas { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px; margin-top: 22px; }
  .cta {
    display: inline-block; padding: 12px 20px; border-radius: 10px; text-decoration: none;
    background: var(--ember); color: #fff; font-weight: 600; font-size: 15px;
  }
  .cta:hover { filter: brightness(1.06); }
  .cta.ghost { background: transparent; color: var(--ink); border: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .cta.ghost:hover { border-color: var(--ember); color: var(--ember); filter: none; }

  .values { color: var(--muted); font-size: 15px; margin-top: 22px; }

  .podcast {
    margin-top: 22px; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-left: 3px solid var(--ember);
    border-radius: 12px; padding: 22px 24px; background: #fff;
  }
  .podcast .show {
    display: block; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px; font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--ember); font-weight: 600;
  }
  .podcast h3 {
    font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(19px, 2.8vw, 23px); line-height: 1.25;
    margin-top: 8px; color: var(--ink);
  }
  .podcast .pmeta { margin-top: 8px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--muted); }
  .listen { margin-top: 16px; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; gap: 8px; }
  .listen-label { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); margin-right: 2px; }
  .plat {
    display: inline-block; padding: 7px 13px; border-radius: 8px; text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 13.5px; font-weight: 600; border: 1px solid var(--line); color: var(--ink);
  }
  .plat:hover { border-color: var(--ember); color: var(--ember); }
  .plat.primary { background: var(--ember); color: #fff; border-color: var(--ember); }
  .plat.primary:hover { filter: brightness(1.06); color: #fff; }

  .press-list { list-style: none; margin: 18px 0 0; padding: 0; display: grid; gap: 8px; }
  .press-list a { font-size: 15px; color: var(--pink-s, var(--ember)); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .press-list a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
